The greatest wit, though not the greatest poet, of our nation;
 and Izaak Walton describes him as-

The busiest time at the Exchange, when it is most worth seeing, is from 3 to 4 P.M. on Tuesdays and Fridays. The eastern part of the building is occupied by Lloyd's, the great rendezvous of ship-owners, and all who seek shipping intelligence. The name originated in the early transaction of the business at Lloyd's Coffee House, at the corner of Abchurch Lane.


If you would wish the world to know,

And learn the state of man;

How some are high and some are low

And human actions scan;

If justly things you would arrange,

And study human heart;

Observe the humours of th« Exchange,

That universal mart.
 --Tom Brown. New London Spy.
